## 🚀 Getting Started

Follow these instructions to get a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

### Prerequisites

* Python 3.8+
* Node.js v14+ and npm
* Git

### Installation

1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```sh
    git clone [https://github.com/sanwu2057-collab/AI-driven-platform.git](https://github.com/sanwu2057-collab/AI-driven-platform.git)
    cd AI-driven-platform
    ```

2.  **Backend Setup:**
    ```sh
    # Navigate to the backend directory
    cd backend

    # Create and activate a virtual environment
    python -m venv venv
    source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`

    # Install dependencies
    pip install -r requirements.txt

    # (Optional) Create a .env file for your environment variables
    # cp .env.example .env

    # Run the server
    uvicorn main:app --reload
    ```
    The backend will be running at `http://127.0.0.1:8000`.

3.  **Frontend Setup:**
    ```sh
    # Open a new terminal and navigate to the frontend directory
    cd frontend

    # Install dependencies
    npm install

    # Run the React app
    npm start
    ```
    The frontend will open in your browser at `http://localhost:3000`.

